  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "There is some danger for the Big Three labs that they have run out of imagination and are now refining Codex/Claude Code/Antigravity, and building their next tools (Cowork, etc) to be similar.\n\nThese were good UX for AI's use &amp; limits today, but not great UX for the future of AI.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2034863643792216182",
    "time": "2026-03-20 13:24",
    "id_str": "2034863643792216182",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Once you are just exploring local maxima, you are doing hill climbing, rather than big innovative leaps.",
